================================================================
PRACTICAL 7(b) - Find Different Controls Using UiPath
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Medium

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will use three "Find" activities:
  (i)  Find Element
  (ii) Find Children
  (iii) Find Ancestor

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

SETUP: Open Notepad (Windows key → Notepad → Enter)

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_7b_FindControls

--- (i) FIND ELEMENT ---

Step 2: Drag a "Find Element" activity into the sequence.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - Click anywhere on the Notepad text area (the big white typing area)
  - UiPath captures the element's selector automatically.

Step 3: In the Output section of Find Element:
  - Click the FoundElement field → press Ctrl+K → name it: foundEl

Step 4: Drag a "Message Box" activity after Find Element.
  - Text: "Element found: " + foundEl.GetType().Name
  - This shows what type of UI element was found.

Step 5: Run (F5).
  - A message box will confirm the element was found.

--- (ii) FIND CHILDREN ---

Step 6: Drag a "Find Children" activity after the Message Box.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - This time, click on the Notepad WINDOW TITLE BAR (the blue bar at the top)
  - This selects the parent window.

Step 7: In the Output → Children field:
  - Press Ctrl+K → name: childList

Step 8: Drag a "Message Box" after Find Children.
  - Text: "Number of child elements: " + childList.Count.ToString
  - This shows how many child UI elements Notepad has.

Step 9: Run (F5).
  - A message box will show the count of children (buttons, text area, etc.)

--- (iii) FIND ANCESTOR ---

Step 10: Drag a "Find Ancestor" activity.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - Click on the Notepad text area (the inner white box)
  - This finds the PARENT of that inner element.

Step 11: In the Output section → press Ctrl+K → name: ancestorEl

Step 12: Drag a "Message Box":
  - Text: "Ancestor found: " + ancestorEl.GetType().Name

Step 13: Run (F5).
  - The ancestor of the text area is the Notepad window itself.

